Solve Barrier: To overcome potential barriers, it is crucial to engage in open communication with the patient, understand his beliefs and concerns, and provide clear and culturally sensitive education on the importance of fluid-intake in managing heart failure. Encouraging regular follow-up appointments and monitoring can also help ensure adherence to recommendations.

Educate: Educate the patient about the importance of maintaining a consistent fluid-intake level, monitoring for signs of fluid retention or worsening heart failure symptoms, and seeking immediate medical attention if any concerns arise. Emphasize the role of fluid management in optimizing his heart health and overall well-being.